@ENDNODE

@NODE WhatItIs "ScreenInWindow/What is this program for?"
@{LINDENT 3}
This  program  shows  a  part  of  a public or private (!) screen in a
window on another (or the same) public or non-public (!) screen!
Additionaly,  the  program/window  on  the  monitored  screen  can  be
controlled @{"remotely" link RemoteCtrl} by SIW!

Thats  usefull  for example if you are reading your emails and want to
watch the download of your terminal program, but didn't want to switch
between the screens!
With @{b}ScreenInWindow@{ub} you  could set up a small window in the upper-right
edge with the interresting part of the screen!

The  window  is  fully sizeable (as large as the monitored screen) and
has  a  vertical and a horizontal slider for choosing the desired part
of the screen!

You  can  'drag'  the  contents  of the window with the left or middle
mousebutton!   Simple press (& hold) the left (or middle) mouse-button
anywhere  in  the  window and move the mouse to change the part of the
screen!
If @{"Remote Control" link RemoteCtrl} is activated then you have to press one of the shift
keys  with the left mousebutton or the middle button without any other
keys.

@ENDNODE

@NODE RemoteCtrl "ScreenInWindow/Remote Control"

@{fg shine}@{b}Remote Control:@{fg text}@{ub}
@{LINDENT 3}
This  feature  lets  you  control  the program on the monitored screen
within @{b}SIW@{ub}s window!

If  @{b}RemoteControl@{ub}  is  enabled,  then  (almost)  all  events  will  be
redirected  to  the  window on the monitored screen which is under the
mouse!
Right   now   menus   aren't  support.   There  are  also  some  other
restrictions, which are explained some lines later.

If you enabled  @{"Emulate Keyboard?" link Arg_EmuKeys} in  the @{b}RemoteControl@{ub}-Menu, then all
keyboard events will be redirected to the window under the mouse.

If you enabled  @{"Emulate Gadgets?" link Arg_EmuGads} in  the @{b}RemoteControl@{ub}-Menu,  then SIW
tries to "emulate" the gadgets in the monitored window.

Restrictions in the gadget emulation:
 - Slider/Proportional gadgets couldn't be remote controlled,
   only the arrow-buttons can be used!
 - System-Window-Gadgets  (drag, depth, zip, size but not (!) close)
   and gadgets that have relative coordinates aren't supported
 - gadtools palette-gadget doesn't work 
 
But  gadtools  button-,  checkmark-,  string-,  listview-  (except the
slider) and the radio-gadget can be remote controlled!

Problems with DOpus v5.5:
 - dragging of icons didn't works 100%...
   It  works  while  the  mouse  is  in  motion,  but if you stop (w/o
   releasing the button), the dragging is aborted. Don't know why...
   The list-titles (name, size, date etc.) can be dragged and switched
   the right way!?
 - listview-items can't be selected,  on some listviews Enforcer shows
   many hits (from DOpus!)
   (GadTools-listview are working....)
 - the  popup-menus of the status line  are drawn way to left, but can
   be controlled!
 - the  string-gadget  at the bottom  edge can't be used, cause it has
   relative coordinates
 - the  other  string-gadget   also  doesn't  work,   cause  they  get
   deactivated as soon as a other window is the active one.
   (intuition/gadtools stringgadgets are working very well!)

@{b}HINT@{ub}:
  If  you  want to remote-control a MUI-Program then you don't have to
  set  the  option  @{b}Emulate Gadgets?@{ub},  cause  MUI didn't uses ordinary
  Intuition-Gadgets!
@ENDNODE

@NODE HowToStart "ScreenInWindow/How to start"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}Start from a shell:@{ub}

   Run @{b}SIW@{ub} @{" MS=MonitorScreen          " link Arg_MonScr   },@{" SCR=HomeScreen          " link Arg_HomeScr   },
           @{" VS=VertStep/K/N           " link Arg_vStep    },@{" HS=HorizStep/K/N        " link Arg_hStep     },
           @{" IU=InactiveUpdateRate/K/N " link Arg_iUpdate  },@{" AU=ActiveUpdateRate/K/N " link Arg_aUpdate   },
           @{" WL=WinLeft/K/N            " link Arg_WinLeft  },@{" WT=WinTop/K/N           " link Arg_WinTop    },
           @{" WW=WinIWidth/K/N          " link Arg_WinIWidth},@{" WH=WinIHeight/K/N       " link Arg_WinIHeight},
           @{" SL=ScrLeft/K/N            " link Arg_ScrLeft  },@{" ST=ScrTop/K/N           " link Arg_ScrTop    },
           @{" VF=VertFactor/K/N         " link Arg_vFac     },@{" HF=HorizFactor/K/N      " link Arg_hFac      },@{" RS=ReverseScroll/S   " link Arg_revScroll},
           @{" RC=RemoteControl/S        " link Arg_RC       },@{" EG=EmulateGadgets/S     " link Arg_EmuGads   },@{" EK=EmulateKeyboard/S " link Arg_EmuKeys  },
           @{" CC=CapsCursors/S          " link Arg_CC       },@{" UAS=UseAllScreens/S     " link Arg_UAS       },
           @{" CX_POPKEY/K               " link Arg_CXPopKey },@{" CX_POPUP/K              " link Arg_CXPopUp   }

@{b}Start from Workbench:@{ub}
  
   No tooltype support yet but you can use prefs-files.
   Try to convince me to implement tooltype-support;-)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_MonScr "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}MS=MonitorScreen@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options  specifies  the public or private screen which should be
monitored.

This  is  optional,  default  is  the  system-default pub-screen (e.g.
"Workbench").

You can also use AmigaOS-Wildcards here to specify the screens name!
The first match will be taken.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_HomeScr "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}SCR=HomeScreen@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This   options  specifies  the  public  or  private  screen  on  which
@{b}ScreenInWindow@{ub} should open its window.

This  is  optional,  default  is  the  system-default pub-screen (e.g.
"Workbench").

You can also use AmigaOS-Wildcards here to specify the screens name!
The first match will be taken.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_vStep "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}VS=VertStep/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options specifies the number of pixels the content of the window
should move if the user presses the up or down button.

This is optional, default is 3 pixels.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_hStep "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}HS=HorizStep/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options specifies the number of pixels the content of the window
should move if the user presses the left or right button.

This is optional, default is 6 pixels.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_iUpdate "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}IU=InactiveUpdateRate/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options  specifies the rate (1/50 secs) how often the content of
the window should get updated if its @{b}inactive@{ub}.

This is optional, default is 50 (every second).

If its 0, the content won't be updated if the window is inactiv!

Maximum value for this option is 500, that means 10 seconds.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_aUpdate "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}AU=ActiveUpdateRate/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options  specifies the rate (1/10 secs) how often the content of
the window should get updated if its @{b}active@{ub}.

This is optional, default is 1 (every 1/10 second).

If its 0, the content will be updated (if the window is activ) only if
the  user  changes  the desired part, that means drag the mouse or use
the gadgets.

Maximum value for this option is 50, that means 10 seconds.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_WinLeft "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}WL=WinLeft/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This options specifies the left edge where the window should open.

This is optional, default is 200.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_WinTop "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}WT=WinTop/K/N@{ub}
This options specifies the top edge where the window should open.

This is optional, default is 100.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_WinIWidth "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}WW=WinIWidth/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This options specifies the inner (w/o borders) width of the window.

This is optional, default is 400.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_WinIHeight "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}WH=WinIHeight/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This options specifies the inner (w/o borders) height of the window.

This is optional, default is 100.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_ScrLeft "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}SL=ScrLeft/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options specifies the left edge of the monitored pubscreen where
monitoring should start.

This is optional, default is 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_ScrTop "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}ST=ScrTop/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options  specifies the top edge of the monitored pubscreen where
monitoring should start.

This is optional, default is 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_vFac "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}VF=VertFactor/K/N@{ub}
This  options  specifies  the  vertical  factor for the @{b}drag-feature@{ub} of
@{b}ScreenInWindow@{ub}.

This is optional, default is MontoredScreen.height / Window.InnerHeight.

Values > 0 will move the content in the direction of the sliders.
Values < 0 will move the content in the direction of the mouse.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_hFac "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}HF=HorizFactor/K/N@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  options  specifies  the horizontal factor for the @{b}drag-feature@{ub} of
@{b}ScreenInWindow@{ub}.

This is optional, default is MonitoredScreen.width / Window.InnerWidth.
   
Values > 0 will move the content in the direction of the sliders.
Values < 0 will move the content in the direction of the mouse.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_revScroll "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}RS=ReverseScroll/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This option is only usefull if @{"VertFactor" link Arg_vFac} and @{"HorizFactor"  link Arg_hFac} aren't
specified are you are using the @{b}drag-feature@{ub}!

If  the  option  is used the content will move in the direction of
the mouse, if not, it will move the sliders.

You should try it!

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_RC "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}RC=RemoteControl/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
Well,  if  this  option  is  used,  the  incoming input-events will be
redirected  to the window on the monitored screen the mouse pointer is
on.

You should try it!

Read also: @{"Remote Control" link RemoteCtrl}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_EmuGads "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}EG=EmulateGadgets/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This   option  tells  SIW  to  emulate  gadgets  if  RemoteControl  is
activated.

Read also: @{"Remote Control" link RemoteCtrl}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_EmuGads "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}EG=EmulateGadgets/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This   option  tells  SIW  to  emulate  gadgets  if  RemoteControl  is
activated.

Read also: @{"Remote Control" link RemoteCtrl}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_EmuKeys "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}EK=EmulateKeyboard/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This option tells SIW to emulate keyboard if RemoteControl is activated.
The events will be sended to the window under the mouse!

Read also: @{"Remote Control" link RemoteCtrl}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_CC "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}CC=CapsCursors/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
If  you  also  want  to  scroll  the  contents  of the window with the
cursorkeys  while  @{"Remote  Control" link RemoteCtrl} and @{"Emulate Keyboard"  link  Arg_EmuKeys} is active,
you have to turn this option on and have the capsLock-key pressed!

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_UAS "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}UAS=UseAllScreens/S@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
If  you  specify this option all screens (not only public-screens) can
be used to be watched and remote-controled and open SIWs window on!

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_CXPopKey "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}CX_POPKEY/K@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This option specifies the key-description, which popups the window, if
it was @{"hidden" link Menus_Project}.

Default is: "Ctrl alt w"

Additionaly  you  can  popup the window by sending the SIW-Process the
signal-F (Break F `Status COM = SIW`) or with Exchange or CxBar.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Arg_CXPopUp "ScreenInWindow/Argument"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}CX_POPUP/K@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
This  option  specifies,  if  the  window  should  be opened (TRUE) on
startup or not (FALSE).

Default is: TRUE, that means the window will be opened.

Example: @{b}CX_POPUP FALSE@{ub} or @{b}CX_POPUP TRUE@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus "ScreenInWindow/Menus"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{fg shine}@{b}ScreenInWindow Menus:@{fg text}@{ub}
@{LINDENT 6}
@{" Project        " link Menus_Project} 
@{" Remote Control " link Menus_RemoteCtrl}
@{" Settings       " link Menus_Settings}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Project "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Project"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Project Menu:@{fg text}
@{LINDENT 3}
Open...     @{fg shine}O@{fg text} @{ub}- Open/load a settings file@{b}
-----------
Save        @{fg shine}S@{fg text} @{ub}- Save the current settings to
                SYS:Prefs/Presets/<HomeScreenName>-<MonitorScreenName>.siw@{b}
Save as...  @{fg shine}A@{fg text} @{ub}- like save, but you can choose the name of the file.
                (via ASL-Requester)
                The  file  will  be overwritten, if there is already a
                file with this name!@{b}
-----------
About...    @{fg shine}?@{fg text} @{ub}- Show some informationen about this program.@{b}
Help...       @{ub}- Open/show the AmigaGuide help document in asynchronous mode.
                You can continue to work with SIW while the AmigaGuide
                window is open!
-----------
Hide        @{fg shine}H@{fg text} @{ub}- Hide the window.
                You can reveal it with "Exchange" or "CxBar", the
                popup-key or with Ctrl-F.@{b}
Quit        @{fg shine}Q@{fg text} @{ub}- Quit the program. Without asking.@{b}

@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_RemoteCtrl ScreenInWindow/Menus/Remote Control"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Remote Control Menu:@{fg text}
@{LINDENT 3}
Enabled?                 @{fg shine}R@{fg text} @{ub}- Enabled remote-control?@{b}
Emulate Gadgets?         @{fg shine}G@{fg text} @{ub}- Should @{"gadgets be emulated" link RemoteCtrl}?@{b}
Emulate Keyboard?        @{fg shine}B@{fg text} @{ub}- Should the @{"keyboard be emulated" link RemoteCtrl}?@{b}
------------------------
CapsLock = Cursorkeys?   @{fg shine}=@{fg text} @{ub}- Use caps and cursorkeys to scroll the contents
                             of the window while remoteCtrl and emuKeys are active?@{b}
Use all screens?         @{fg shine}U@{fg text} @{ub}- Use all screens not only public-screens?@{b}
Focus on current window? @{fg shine}F@{fg text} @{ub}- Watch/remote-ctrl only a window not the whole screen?{b}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Einstellungen"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Settings Menu:@{ub}@{fg text}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{" Home Screen          " link Menus_Settings_HomeScr}
@{" Monitor Screen       " link Menus_Settings_MonScr}

@{" Inactive Update-Rate " link Menus_Settings_IUpdate}
@{" Active Update-Rate   " link Menus_Settings_AUpdate}

@{" Vertical Step        " link Menus_Settings_VertStep}
@{" Horizontal Step      " link Menus_Settings_HorizStep}

@{" Vert. Scroll-Factor  " link Menus_Settings_VertFactor}
@{" Horiz. Scroll-Factor " link Menus_Settings_HorizFactor}

@{" Lock Direction       " link Menus_Settings_LockDir}
@{" Misc.                " link Menus_Settings_Misc}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_HomeScr "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Homat Screen"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the screen where SIW should open his window:@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_HomeScr}
@{LINDENT 3}
Choose...  @{fg shine}L@{fg text} @{ub}- You can choose a public screen out of a listview!@{b}
Next       @{fg shine}K@{fg text} @{ub}- Open the window on the next public screen.@{b}

@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_MonScr "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Monitor Screen"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the screen which should be watched/remote-controled:@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_MonScr}
@{LINDENT 3}
Choose...  @{fg shine},@{fg text} @{ub}- You can choose a public screen out of a listview!@{b}
Next       @{fg shine}M@{fg text} @{ub}- Watch the next public screen.@{b}

@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_IUpdate "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Inactive Update-Rate"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the update rate (1/50 secs) if the window is inactive:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_iUpdate}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}           - Increment it by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}           - Increment it by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}           - Decrement it by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}           - Decrement it by 5
@{b}...@{ub}          - Call a string requester to enter a value.
               Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=50/50 (Def)@{ub} - Set it to 50/50 secs, that means 1 second
@{b}=1/50@{ub}        - Set it to 1/50 secs
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_AUpdate "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Active Update-Rate"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the update rate (1/10 secs) if the window is active:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_aUpdate}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}           - Increment it by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}           - Increment it by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}           - Decrement it by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}           - Decrement it by 5
@{b}...@{ub}          - Call a string requester to enter a value.
               Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=10/10 (Def)@{ub} - Set it to 10/10 secs, that means 1 second
@{b}=1/10@{ub}        - Set it to 1/10 secs

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_VertStep "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Vertical Step"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the number of pixels the content should move if up or down is pressed:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_vStep}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}       - Increment them by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}       - Increment them by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}       - Decrement them by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}       - Decrement them by 5
@{b}...@{ub}      - Call a string requester to enter a value.
           Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=3 (def)@{ub} - Set it to 3 (default)
@{b}=1@{ub}       - Set it to 1 pixel
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_HorizStep "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Horizontal Step"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the number of pixels the content should move if left or right is pressed:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_hStep}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}       - Increment them by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}       - Increment them by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}       - Decrement them by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}       - Decrement them by 5
@{b}...@{ub}      - Call a string requester to enter a value.
           Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=6 (Def)@{ub} - Set it to 6 (default)
@{b}=1@{ub}       - Set it to 1 pixel
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_VertFactor "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Vert. Scroll-Factor"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the vertical factor for the drag-feature:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_vFac}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}      - Increment it by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}      - Increment it by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}      - Decrement it by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}      - Decrement it by 5
@{b}default@{ub} - If @{"HorizFactor" link Arg_hFac} is specified on startup, then it will be set
          to this value. If not, it will be set relativ to windows size.
@{b}...@{ub}     - Call a string requester to enter a value.
          Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=1@{ub}      - Set it to 1 pixel
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_HorizFactor "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Horiz. Scroll-Factor"

@{fg shine}@{b}Change the horizontal factor for the drag-feature:@{ub}@{fg text}@{" see also here " link Arg_hFac}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}+5@{ub}      - Increment it by 5
@{b}+1@{ub}      - Increment it by 1
@{b}-1@{ub}      - Decrement it by 1
@{b}-5@{ub}      - Decrement it by 5
@{b}default@{ub} - If @{"VertFactor" link Arg_vFac} is specified on startup, then it will be set to this
          value. If not, it will be set relativ to windows size.
@{b}...@{ub}     - Call a string requester to enter a value.
          Only available if reqtools.library is available!
@{b}=1@{ub}      - Set it to 1 pixel
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_LockDir "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Lock Direction"

@{fg shine}@{b}Set the direction which should be locked if you drag the content:@{ub}@{fg text}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}None@{ub}       - None will be locked
@{b}Horizontal@{ub} - Lock horizontal movement
@{b}Vertical@{ub}   - Lock vertical movement
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus_Settings_Misc "ScreenInWindow/Menus/Settings/Misc"

@{fg shine}@{b}These are some misc. options:@{ub}@{fg text}
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}Reverse scroll?@{ub} - Toggle the direction for the drag-feature
@{b}Relativ scroll?@{ub} - Set the scroll factors for the drag-feature relativ to the
                  windows size
@{b}Show values?@{ub}    - Show some parameters in the screen title bar
@ENDNODE

@NODE Register "ScreenInWindow/Registering"
@{LINDENT 3}
You only have to fill out the @{"register formular" link Registration.txt} and send it to me.
@{"Via eMail or snail mail" link Me}.

The  share for @{b}ScreenInWindow@{ub} is $10, 10DM or the appropriate amount of
your countries money.
@{"You can transfer it to my bank-account or send it in cash." link Me}

In the @{b}unregistered@{ub} version are the following options disabled:
 - @{"Project/Save"                          link Menus_Project}
 - @{"Project/Save as..."                    link Menus_Project}
 - @{"Project/Hide"                          link Menus_Project}
 - @{"Project/Options/Home Screen/Choose..." link Menus_Settings_HomeScr}
